    Ann Oncol
    External Control Arms in Oncology: Current Use and Future Directions.
When a randomized design is not possible, incorporating external control data into the study design can be an effective way to expand the interpretability of the results of an experimental arm by introducing the ability to perform a formal or informal comparative analysis. This manuscript provides an introduction to the concepts of external controls in oncology trials, followed by a review of relevant and current research on this topic. The paper also focuses on general considerations for designing a trial that may incorporate external control data, followed by case studies of the marketing applications submitted to the FDA that included external control data.
